{
  "texts": [
    "97 Han et al. [126] 2023 Health \"AI hallucination\" occurs when AI confidently generates an impressive-sounding response that may not be justified by its training data or may even be factually incorrect.",
    "98 Dolan and Freer [127] 2023 Academia \"AI hallucination\" refers to the phenomenon where AI systems may create or invent text and citations that sound realistic but are not based on actual information, and in certain instances, they may even fabricate nonexistent works.",
    "99 Scott-Branch et al. [128] 2023 Academia \"AI hallucination\" refers to mistakes in the generated text that are semantically or syntactically plausible but are in fact incorrect or nonsensical.",
    "100 Larsen-Ledet [129] 2023 Academia \"AI hallucination\" refers to the generation of output, often text, containing falsities, which undermine the intended factual nature of the service, intended to be reliable and trustworthy.",
    "Continued on next pageTABLE V -continued from previous page Num."
  ]
}